  "content": "\u003cp\u003eThink of how much waste there is throwing out yearly calendars because we don\u0026#39;t use 13 months, each having 28 days (with new years being monthless). I remember talking about this 15 years ago. It still makes way more sense than our current system.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt better aligns to moon cycles (the original purpose of months). It makes weeks align perfectly into months so Monday can always start each month. Every year is the same. No more printing calendars that just work for a specific year.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eLeap year days aren\u0026#39;t added to a random month. It will be monthless, like New Year\u0026#39;s day. New year\u0026#39;s day can just be two days long on leap years. ðŸ¥³ ðŸŽ‰\u003c/p\u003e",
